      <body>
        <div>
            <pb facs="#TL-0409.jpg" n="part3_p017.jpg" xml:id="img_0017" corresp="https://id.acdh.oeaw.ac.at/tillich-lectures/part3_p017.jpg"/>
            
            <p facs="#facs_17_tr_3">
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_1" n="N001"/> Ma¬
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_2" n="N002"/>LECTURE XXXII, March 6, 956
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_3" n="N003"/>Now here are two interesting questions. I will try to answer them:
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_4" n="N004"/>QN: If religion cannot be defended on the object-subject level of reality, can there be such a being
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_5" n="N005"/>as apologetics?
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_6" n="N006"/>PT: Now the word "apolostics" can have many Seanings, and most Neo-Ormodox theologians
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_3_tl_7" n="N007"/>are very suspicious of ANY kind of apologetics. I personally would say it depends on theAPOLOGETISS.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_17_tr_2">
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_1" n="N001"/>The word in itself is the highest possible word in theology—a biblical word, and a church-historial
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_2" n="N002"/>word. It means: answers. And if a Christian is not able to answer, then he shouldn’t try to make
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_3" n="N003"/>theology. That is the one answer to it.
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_4" n="N004"/>But now the next question is what KIND of apologetics? There the answer is: NOT an
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_5" n="N005"/>out of the subject-object structure of reality,
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_6" n="N006"/>apologetic which trees to drive,
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_7" n="N007"/>the existence of God, or immortality, or other things—this kind of apologetics is not only impossible
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_8" n="N008"/>but it is even an a priori negation of the idea of God, whatever the outcome of such argument is.
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_9" n="N009"/>The analysis of reality can only lead to the QUESTION of God—which MEANS Very MUCH
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_10" n="N010"/>because there is no question without a preceding answer; but it certainly does NOT mean a
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_2_tl_11" n="N011"/>rational deduction of God out of the world of the limite in which subject-object structure prevails.
            </p>
            <p facs="#facs_17_tr_1">
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_1" n="N001"/>So the only kind of apologetics which is possible seems to me the fortlopment of the question
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_2" n="N002"/>and to point out that the answers involved in the Christian tradition are REAL ANDWERS to
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_3" n="N003"/>REAL QUESTIONS. And this apologetic is nothing else than systematic theolog.
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_4" n="N004"/>Now this was the one [question]. The next question is a little bit too long, but I will
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_5" n="N005"/>try to do it:
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_6" n="N006"/>QN (P.H.John): in his recent book, lcon and Idea, Sir Herbert Road says that the history of art
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_7" n="N007"/>and the history of ideas have hitherto been considered as independent aspects of humanòvelopment,
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_8" n="N008"/>and priority was given to ideas. But he says that in reality the plastic image—or icon—always precedes
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_9" n="N009"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_10" n="N010"/>cette
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_11" n="N011"/>Monsieur Mounard, car cʼest
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_12" n="N012"/>dʼune manière beaucoup
               <lb facs="#facs_17_tr_1_tl_13" n="N013"/>dʼadresse
            </p>
            
